Package edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.util

Class LinkedAbstractList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.util.LinkedAbstractList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The class that the list can store in the nodes
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.List<E>
    public class LinkedAbstractList<E>
extends java.util.AbstractList<E>
    This is a basic abstract Linked List implementation, allowing for a generic data type to be stored in nodes, up to a certain capacity. You can add, edit, remove, and get data from nodes based off their index. You can also see the current size of the LinkedList.
    Author:
    Marshall Pearson
